<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="639" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/25424:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General in Martinique (<persName type="from">Malige</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort-de-France</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-10T18:00:00-04:00">November
                                    10, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>479. From Reber. My 473, November 8, and 478, November 10.<note n="10" xml:id="d639fn10">Latter not printed.</note> Robert has just
                            informed me that Vichy has expressed its desire that he maintain
                            relations with the United States on the basis of the agreement reached
                            November 7 and has entrusted him with carrying on official relations of
                            the French possessions in the Western Hemisphere. [Reber.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Malige</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>